See: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Permissions-Policy** + ///etc/hosts: The server install allows reading of any system file by adding an extra '/' to the URL. + /wp-content/themes/twentyeleven/images/headers/server.php?filesrc=/etc/hosts: A PHP backdoor file manager was found. + /wordpress/wp-content/themes/twentyeleven/images/headers/server.php?filesrc=/etc/hosts: A PHP backdoor file manager was found. + /wp-includes/Requests/Utility/content-post.php?filesrc=/etc/hosts: A PHP backdoor file manager was found. + /wordpress/wp-includes/Requests/Utility/content-post.php?filesrc=/etc/hosts: A PHP backdoor file manager was found. + /wp-includes/js/tinymce/themes/modern/Meuhy.php?filesrc=/etc/hosts: A PHP backdoor file manager was found. + /wordpress/wp-includes/js/tinymce/themes/modern/Meuhy.php?filesrc=/etc/hosts: A PHP backdoor file manager was found. + /assets/mobirise/css/meta.php?filesrc=: A PHP backdoor file manager was found. + /login.cgi?cli=aa%20aa%27cat%20/etc/hosts: Some D-Link router remote command execution. + /shell?cat+/etc/hosts: A backdoor was identified. + 7866 requests: 7 error(s) and 15 item(s) reported on remote host + End Time: 2025-08-17 16:09:33 (GMT9) (96 seconds) ``` - GPT 질의결과 볼드처리한 headers를 제외한 취약점들은 **오탐으로 판명되었음** - Nikto에서 권장되는 헤더를 추가하는 `custom_rule.conf` 작성 ```bash ## HEADERS ----------------------------------------------------------------------- # 콘텐츠 타입 스니핑 방지 add_header x-content-type-options "nosniff" always; # HSTS: 모든 연결을 HTTPS로 강제 (HTTPS 필수) # TODO: HTTPS 적용 후 설정 # add_header Strict-Transport-Security "max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains" always; # Referrer 정보 전송 차단 add_header referrer-policy "no-referrer" always; charset=utf-8 Content-Length: 12 Connection: keep-alive X-Powered-By: Express ETag: W/"c-00hq6RNueFa8QiEjhep5cJRHWAI" Access-Control-Allow-Headers: * x-content-type-options: nosniff referrer-policy: no-referrer content-security-policy: default-src 'self' permissions-policy: camera=(), microphone=() Hello world!% ``` - Nikto에서 권장하는 헤더가 잘 셋팅되어 오는것을 확인, 재스캔시 **`Suggested security header missing`** 를 탐지하지 않는것을 확인 # Zap ## 취약점 검사 ## 보완 1. PII Disclosure (Risk: HIGH) - https://www.zaproxy.org/docs/alerts/10062/ - 요약: 응답에는 신용카드 번호, 주민등록번호 및 이와 유사한 민감한 데이터와 같은 개인 식별 정보가 포함되어 있는 취약점. - ZAP 에서 제안하는 해결: 개인 식별 정보(PII)가 포함되어 있을 가능성이 있는지 응답을 확인하고, 애플리케이션을 통해 중요한 정보가 유출되지 않도록 합니다. - 해결 방법: 아래 룰 추가 ```bash # ModSecurity 응답 본문 검사 활성화 SecResponseBodyAccess On ``` 2. issue.title: Support running psycopg test suite with pytest-xdist
issue.body:
On my computer (a recent AMD Ryzen 9 HX 370), `pytest` takes about 8 minutes. When run with `-n auto` (this computer has 12 cores/24 threads), it takes 50s. So it seems worthwhile to make pytest-xdist work, but feel free to close the issue if you are not interested in this. There are two issues: 1. The [`segfault` detection](https://github.com/psycopg/psycopg/blob/7671556413ca4b94911ef2032d5f1be6140c28e1/tests/conftest.py#L59-L69) in conftest.py is not compatible with xdist; the cache is shared among the the controller and all workers, so the workers immediately assume a segfault occurred and refuse to run. The solution is to only do it on the controller. 2. Some tests fail, presumably because of interference from other concurrently-running tests (see example list below). The solution is either to make the tests not interfere with each other, or just make each worker run in its own DB instead of all running in against a single shared DB (this is the approach pytest-django uses for example). I haven't looked at this yet.

comment.body:
The test suite is not designed to be concurrent. Tests may try to access the same database object (drop table foo if exists... Create table foo).

I don't have desire to maintain parallel tests which on random run may interact in unexpected way. Not going to pay this price. If you want to propose a parallel solution you must propose a fully automated way to run tests in separate databases, otherwise this is a non-starter. If you are committed to make this change that's ok, otherwise please close this ticket.

You can run your test with purest -m "not slow" on your machine.

pull_request.title: feat: index.js refactoring, real-time save settings, add settings snapshots, chat room renaming and bug fixes
pull_request.body:
This pull request introduces a major refactoring of the codebase to a component-based architecture, along with new features and several bug fixes.

Key changes include:

**Features:**
- Implement real-time settings and snapshot management:
    - Settings now save on input change with debouncing for performance.
    - New settings snapshot feature to automatically save up to 10 previous versions.
    - Improved "Cancel" button in settings to revert unsaved changes with confirmation.
- Inline Chat Room Renaming: 
    - Implemented inline editing for chat room names 
    - Includes a confirm button for explicit save and hides non-essential UI elements during rename.

**Refactoring:**
- Decompose index.js into a component-based structure:
    - UI rendering logic extracted into `src/components/`.
    - New `src/ui.js` for component rendering orchestration.
    - Event handling moved to `src/handlers/`.
    - Utilities separated into `api.js`, `storage.js`, `utils.js`.
- Pass prompts explicitly to API calls and add transparent favicons.
- Refactored API calls to use an options object for improved clarity and maintainability.
- Improved error handling and code readability in storage and utility functions.
- Used handler mapping for `handleModalInput`.

**Bug Fixes:**
- Apply font scale on page load.
- Correct errors in random first talk feature.
- Prevent message input loss on new character addition.
- Correct backup and restore logic in storage:
    - `handleBackup` now sources data from live application state to prevent data loss.
    - `handleRestore` now correctly restores `chatRooms` and `userStickers` with fallback defaults.
- Fix issues identified during refactoring:
    - UI rendering on initial load.
    - Removed call to non-existent `addKeyboardListeners`.
- Fixed a critical bug where chat room name changes were not persisted due to incorrect state mutation.
- Resolved an issue where the inline editing UI for chat rooms would not appear correctly.
- Fixed a bug causing the chat room deletion modal to remain open after completion.
- Addressed issues with character edit/delete modals not appearing immediately, ensuring correct state change detection. 
    - Prevented settings modal from resetting/collapsing during auto-save by moving snapshot creation to an explicit save action. 
    - Fixed character deletion confirmation modal not closing.
- Added a 500ms debounce to settings inputs to prevent UI lag and excessive re-rendering.
- Corrected event handling for character edit and delete buttons in the sidebar.
- Changed `checkStorageSpace` warning limit (renamed to `getLocalStorageFallbackUsage`).
- Applied fixes based on PR review.

issue.title: Stress when dropping Torch and using your weapon
issue.body: Stress when dropping Torch and using your weapon. I don't think that is the game design. I think the idea is to only have to Burden worth of Weapon, Stress to switch in another for another rider or whatever -- range or the likes.

comment.body:
I would agree that sometimes, as a special case, telling the story of a especially harrowing situation, costs or risks might make sense, asking for
- a `Reaction Roll`
- marking `Stress`,
maybe the former to avoid the latter? Keep it simple though, I think the above (no cost) is the rule, other rulings should be for special cases supporting the story.
